00:31:57.170 --> 00:31:59.697 align:middle line:10%
Navigating uncertainty
with chaos as your guide,

00:31:59.697 --> 00:32:00.530 align:middle line:10%
what does that mean?

00:32:00.530 --> 00:32:01.840 align:middle line:10%
MARTINEZ: That sounds
crazy, doesn't it?

00:32:01.840 --> 00:32:02.420 align:middle line:10%
LISA: Yeah.

00:32:02.420 --> 00:32:04.190 align:middle line:10%
MARTINEZ: But what
happens is uncertainty

00:32:04.190 --> 00:32:05.120 align:middle line:10%
is there all the time.

00:32:05.120 --> 00:32:07.409 align:middle line:10%
We create order in the world.

00:32:07.409 --> 00:32:08.450 align:middle line:10%
The world is not ordered.

00:32:08.450 --> 00:32:09.250 align:middle line:10%
We create order.

00:32:09.250 --> 00:32:11.250 align:middle line:10%
We go from A to B. And
we think that this order,

00:32:11.250 --> 00:32:13.166 align:middle line:10%
because it's the left
side of the brain that's

00:32:13.166 --> 00:32:13.970 align:middle line:10%
causing sequence.

00:32:13.970 --> 00:32:15.510 align:middle line:84%
But the world is
basically chaotic.

00:32:15.510 --> 00:32:18.950 align:middle line:90%
And chaotic is not random.

00:32:18.950 --> 00:32:21.470 align:middle line:84%
Chaotic is from
complexity theory.

00:32:21.470 --> 00:32:25.102 align:middle line:10%
It's really disordered order.

00:32:25.102 --> 00:32:26.435 align:middle line:90%
But it has a different geometry.

00:32:26.435 --> 00:32:27.780 align:middle line:90%
It's not Euclidean.

00:32:27.780 --> 00:32:28.580 align:middle line:90%
LISA: It's random.

00:32:28.580 --> 00:32:31.430 align:middle line:90%


00:32:31.430 --> 00:32:34.730 align:middle line:10%
MARTINEZ: Random would be
that it has no predictability.

00:32:34.730 --> 00:32:36.020 align:middle line:10%
Chaos has predictability.

00:32:36.020 --> 00:32:40.640 align:middle line:10%
But like, for example,
when you're boiling water,

00:32:40.640 --> 00:32:42.980 align:middle line:10%
you see bubbles coming
and they're predictable.

00:32:42.980 --> 00:32:48.260 align:middle line:10%
But when chaos comes in,
there's a bifurcation

00:32:48.260 --> 00:32:51.230 align:middle line:10%
that that becomes chaotic,
not random, but chaotic.

00:32:51.230 --> 00:32:55.280 align:middle line:84%
When the temperature goes
down, it goes back to linear.

00:32:55.280 --> 00:32:56.690 align:middle line:90%
So what happens?

00:32:56.690 --> 00:32:59.150 align:middle line:90%
You're driving around.

00:32:59.150 --> 00:33:03.530 align:middle line:84%
And in LA this will
be a very frequent.

00:33:03.530 --> 00:33:05.090 align:middle line:90%
You're stuck in traffic--

00:33:05.090 --> 00:33:06.456 align:middle line:90%
LISA: Like that out there.

00:33:06.456 --> 00:33:07.580 align:middle line:90%
MARTINEZ: Stuck in traffic.

00:33:07.580 --> 00:33:11.060 align:middle line:10%
So you were predicting that
you were going to get there

00:33:11.060 --> 00:33:12.710 align:middle line:10%
on time without the traffic.

00:33:12.710 --> 00:33:14.690 align:middle line:10%
So it's a predictive mode.

00:33:14.690 --> 00:33:15.710 align:middle line:10%
That's linear.

00:33:15.710 --> 00:33:18.324 align:middle line:10%
The moment that the
complexity comes in,

00:33:18.324 --> 00:33:20.240 align:middle line:10%
the moment that bifurcation
comes in and says,

00:33:20.240 --> 00:33:23.060 align:middle line:10%
no, no, you're going to be
stuck here, this is different.

00:33:23.060 --> 00:33:27.080 align:middle line:10%
Then you go from
confirmation to discovery.

00:33:27.080 --> 00:33:29.420 align:middle line:10%
And you stop and you
look for novelty.

00:33:29.420 --> 00:33:31.670 align:middle line:10%
How am I breathing now?

00:33:31.670 --> 00:33:33.739 align:middle line:90%
Could I go a different way?

00:33:33.739 --> 00:33:35.780 align:middle line:84%
What kind of music would
I like to listen to now?

00:33:35.780 --> 00:33:37.370 align:middle line:90%
So what you do is you divert.

00:33:37.370 --> 00:33:40.460 align:middle line:84%
But you go into discovery,
not confirmation.

00:33:40.460 --> 00:33:42.740 align:middle line:84%
Confirmation is how can
I get out of here, how

00:33:42.740 --> 00:33:44.330 align:middle line:84%
can I get out of
here, instead of what

00:33:44.330 --> 00:33:46.380 align:middle line:90%
can I find in this moment?

00:33:46.380 --> 00:33:48.650 align:middle line:10%
And your brain, when
you go into discovery,

00:33:48.650 --> 00:33:51.200 align:middle line:10%
you go into what's
called mindfulness.

00:33:51.200 --> 00:33:53.780 align:middle line:10%
You release the tension and
you might discover something.

